As illustrated in Fig.~\ref{Fig:point_is_in_either_the_tf_or_the_sf} the two-dimensional field at every point in the problem space is either in the total field or it is not; no point lies on the border. Therefore, if a point is in the total field but it uses points outside to calculate the spatial derivatives when updating its value, it must be modified. The same is true in case a point lying just outside that uses points inside the total field. A plane wave generated in one plane of the three-dimensional problem space, in this case an $XZ$ plane, at $j=ja$ and subtracted out at $j=jb$. Therefore, in free space with no obstacle in the total field, we should see only $E_z$ and $H_x$. The plane wave is generated at one side and subtracted out at other side by adding to $E$ or $H$ fields that are on the boundary and subtracting from $E$ or $H$ fields that are next to the boundary. For the three dimensional case, there is additional surface at $k=ka$ and $k=kb$. The Fig.~\ref{Fig:total_scattered_field_3d} illustrates the $k=ka$ \& $k=kb$ boundaries. For this reason it is needed to make these modifications for the incident array. The modifications are:
\begin{enumerate}
\item The $E_y$ value at $k=ka$ \& $k=kb$:
\begin{subequations}\label{tf_sf_modified_3d_1}
\begin{align}
E_y\left(i,j+1/2,ka\right)&=E_y\left(i,j+1/2,ka\right)-0.5\cdot H_{x\_inc}\left(j\right)\\
E_y\left(i,j+1/2,kb+1\right)&=E_y\left(i,j+1/2,kb+1\right)+0.5\cdot H_{x\_inc}\left(j\right)
\end{align}
\end{subequations}

\item The $E_z$ value at $j=ja$ \& $j=jb$:
\begin{subequations}\label{tf_sf_modified_1}
\begin{align}
E_z\left(i,j_a,k+1/2\right)&=E_z\left(i,j_a,k+1/2\right)+0.5\cdot H_{x\_inc}\left(j_a-1/2\right)\\
E_z\left(i,j_b,k+1/2\right)&=E_z\left(i,j_b,k+1/2\right)-0.5\cdot H_{x\_inc}\left(j_b+1/2\right)
\end{align}
\end{subequations}

\item The $H_x$ field just outside $j=ja$ \& $j=jb:$
\begin{subequations}\label{tf_sf_modified_2}
\begin{align}
H_x\left(i,j_a-1/2,k\right)&=H_x\left(i,j_a-1/2,k\right)+0.5\cdot E_{z\_inc}\left(j_a\right)\\
H_x\left(i,j_b+1/2,k\right)&=H_x\left(i,j_b+1/2,k\right)-0.5\cdot E_{z\_inc}\left(j_b\right)
\end{align}
\end{subequations}

\item The $H_y$ field just outside $i=ia$ \& $i=ib:$
\begin{subequations}\label{tf_sf_modified_3}
\begin{align}
H_y\left(i_a-1/2,j,k\right)&=H_x\left(i_a-1/2,j,k\right)-0.5\cdot E_{z\_inc}\left(j_a\right)\\
H_y\left(i_b+1/2,j,k\right)&=H_x\left(i_b+1/2,j,k\right)+0.5\cdot E_{z\_inc}\left(j_b\right)
\end{align}
\end{subequations}
\end{enumerate}





















